    Scope and Contents
Mrs. Chester Scott discusses life in Michigan and Illinois: growing up, schools, and family in Albion and Cooks, Michigan; marriage to Chester Scott; entertainment and life in Chicago; her work in graduate school as a research assistant in dietary studies at the University of Chicago; community services; Methodist Churches; and family, schools, and community in Chatham, Illinois.5 tapes, 450 mins., 2 vols., 146 pp.
Interview by Judy Mason, 1987
